================================================================================
THIRD-PARTY DATA, IMAGERY & SOFTWARE
================================================================================

The MIT license above covers the RaceIQ source code in this repository. It does
NOT extend to the third-party data, imagery, or software listed below, each of
which is independently licensed by its owner. RaceIQ is an independent project
and is NOT affiliated with Formula 1, the FIA, or any team; "F1" and
"Formula 1" are trademarks of their respective owners. The detailed, regularly
maintained breakdown lives in `docs/DATA_SOURCES.md`.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Data sources
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- FastF1 telemetry & timing — accessed via the open-source FastF1 library
  (MIT-licensed). The underlying timing data is the property of Formula One
  World Championship Limited and is used here under fair use for non-commercial
  predictive modelling.
- Jolpica / Ergast-compatible historical archive — accessed via the Jolpica
  public API (a community mirror of the retired Ergast API). Underlying data is
  sourced from publicly-published race classifications (open data, CC0).
- Open-Meteo — free weather forecast API (planned/optional wiring; see
  `docs/DATA_SOURCES.md`).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Imagery
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- Circuit photography (calendar page) — sourced from Wikimedia Commons under
  various Creative Commons licences (CC BY-SA 3.0, CC BY 4.0, CC0), including
  Planet Labs Inc. "SkySat" satellite aerials. Each URL is anchored to its
  source page in `website/src/lib/raceArt.ts`. The curated URL manifest itself
  (the list of URLs, not the underlying photos) is released under CC0.
- Driver headshots — under `website/public/headshots/`, derived from
  publicly-published team and Formula One promotional imagery, used under fair
  use for non-commercial analytical visualisation. No claim of original
  authorship is made.
- Team logos — under `website/public/team-logos/`, trademarks of their
  respective owners, used for identification under fair use.
- Country flags — fetched at build time from flagcdn.com.

If you are a rights-holder for any image referenced here and would like it
removed or re-attributed, please open an issue in this repository.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Software dependencies (each under its own license)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Frontend:
  Next.js (MIT), React (MIT), Tailwind CSS (MIT), Recharts (MIT),
  @visx/* (MIT), Framer Motion (MIT), GSAP (GreenSock no-charge license),
  Lenis (MIT), Magic UI (MIT), Lucide (ISC), Satori + @resvg/resvg-js (MIT),
  Sharp (Apache-2.0), Playwright (Apache-2.0), Prettier (MIT), ESLint (MIT).

Backend / ML:
  scikit-learn (BSD-3), XGBoost (Apache-2.0), LightGBM (MIT), PyTorch (BSD),
  pandas + NumPy (BSD), DuckDB (MIT), Matplotlib (PSF-based), seaborn (BSD),
  Pillow (HPND/MIT-CMU), pytest (MIT), Ruff (MIT), mypy (MIT).

